1
00:00:09,398 --> 00:00:11,330
I guess I realized it too late, didn't I?

2
00:00:11,506 --> 00:00:12,506
No.

3
00:00:12,637 --> 00:00:14,659
Even if you had realized it sooner,

4
00:00:14,869 --> 00:00:16,800
my answer would've been the same.

5
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:18,188
It has to be him.

6
00:00:18,263 --> 00:00:23,641
So that means I just have to wait until I finish
the race, and then you'll agree to be my boyfriend.

7
00:00:29,256 --> 00:00:30,272
He's in.

8
00:00:30,425 --> 00:00:31,481
He won!

9
00:00:33,912 --> 00:00:34,500
Thit!

10
00:00:34,897 --> 00:00:39,285
- Arthit!
- I can't lose you. I really can't lose you.

11
00:00:50,110 --> 00:00:51,750
I've had someone look into it.

12
00:00:52,114 --> 00:00:53,750
It was that side's doing.

13
00:00:54,130 --> 00:00:56,300
They were probably scared
of losing a lot of money.

14
00:00:56,950 --> 00:00:57,970
Should I handle it?

15
00:00:58,190 --> 00:00:59,550
No need for you to step in.

16
00:01:00,420 --> 00:01:02,290
I won't let them get away with this.

17
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:06,120
Good thing Arthit's tough as hell.

18
00:01:06,270 --> 00:01:08,210
After all that, it's nothing too serious.

19
00:01:08,990 --> 00:01:12,300
He'll wake up soon and come
collect that promise from Daotok.

20
00:01:19,070 --> 00:01:20,080
It's fine.

21
00:01:21,720 --> 00:01:22,720
North.

22
00:01:23,620 --> 00:01:26,180
What if he doesn't wake up, North?

23
00:01:27,900 --> 00:01:29,400
Don't think like that.

24
00:01:30,490 --> 00:01:32,120
P'Arthit's tough as nails.

25
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:36,450
He said.

26
00:01:37,420 --> 00:01:38,930
I should wait for him to win,

27
00:01:40,330 --> 00:01:42,340
and then he'd ask me to be his boyfriend.

28
00:01:43,270 --> 00:01:45,060
And I'm waiting right here.

29
00:01:45,710 --> 00:01:46,710
Calm down.

30
00:01:48,700 --> 00:01:49,700
Why?

31
00:01:50,420 --> 00:01:52,230
I've never seen you cry.

32
00:01:53,214 --> 00:01:54,830
You're gonna make me cry too.

33
00:01:56,070 --> 00:01:57,070
North.

34
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:04,640
P'Thit's been waiting
forever for you to accept him.

35
00:02:05,020 --> 00:02:07,420
With that determination,
he's not dying that easily.

36
00:02:07,850 --> 00:02:09,620
But if something does happen,

37
00:02:10,280 --> 00:02:12,380
I'll find you someone better.

38
00:02:13,007 --> 00:02:14,007
Ouch.

39
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:15,940
I just don't want you to stress out.

40
00:02:20,490 --> 00:02:22,190
Damn it, North.

41
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:25,520
- Hey! Shit! P'Arthit's awake!
- North.

42
00:02:28,485 --> 00:02:29,485
P'Thit.

43
00:02:30,762 --> 00:02:32,574
P'Jo, Uncle Direk.

44
00:02:33,014 --> 00:02:34,819
Uh, doctor!

45
00:02:35,087 --> 00:02:36,477
Wait, I'll go get them.

46
00:02:43,082 --> 00:02:44,082
I missed you.

47
00:04:17,946 --> 00:04:20,365
Thit, you idiot. You dumb buffalo.

48
00:04:20,613 --> 00:04:22,053
Why don't you take care of yourself.

49
00:04:22,882 --> 00:04:24,749
I'm awake now, Direk.

50
00:04:26,048 --> 00:04:28,690
No comforting words? No “there, there”?

51
00:04:29,057 --> 00:04:30,497
Come here and I'll kick you instead.

52
00:04:31,444 --> 00:04:33,688
You almost gave your father a heart attack.

53
00:04:33,847 --> 00:04:36,434
I'm awake now. Calm down.

54
00:04:38,134 --> 00:04:39,814
Guess there's nothing to worry about then.

55
00:04:39,948 --> 00:04:41,099
What a shame.

56
00:04:41,368 --> 00:04:44,385
Hey, North. Am I not your brother? Huh?

57
00:04:46,432 --> 00:04:47,432
Jo.

58
00:04:47,848 --> 00:04:48,848
Shit.

59
00:04:49,001 --> 00:04:50,840
Guess I can't go on ward duty then.

60
00:04:50,979 --> 00:04:52,601
Damn, that sucks.

61
00:04:52,952 --> 00:04:55,548
- Then have Fah submit my leave for me.
- Fine.

62
00:04:56,078 --> 00:04:57,768
If there's nothing else, we'll head out.

63
00:04:57,845 --> 00:04:59,685
Looks like you've got
something to talk about.

64
00:05:00,782 --> 00:05:02,610
Jo, my friend. You're a real one.

65
00:05:04,571 --> 00:05:05,961
Ow.

66
00:05:06,478 --> 00:05:07,478
Jo, you asshole.

67
00:05:08,321 --> 00:05:09,321
Uncle.

68
00:05:09,779 --> 00:05:10,779
Goodbye, Uncle.

69
00:05:11,762 --> 00:05:12,762
See you.

70
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:14,360
What's with him acting all cute?

71
00:05:15,151 --> 00:05:16,151
Hey.

72
00:05:17,122 --> 00:05:18,157
Aren't you going home?

73
00:05:18,432 --> 00:05:21,168
Can't I stay and witness this?

74
00:05:21,242 --> 00:05:22,242
Oh please.

75
00:05:25,838 --> 00:05:30,148
Direk, he won't say
anything because you're here.

76
00:05:32,591 --> 00:05:33,591
Mm.

77
00:05:33,854 --> 00:05:34,617
Fine, I'll go.

78
00:05:34,877 --> 00:05:36,869
I'll come back tomorrow for your check-up.

79
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,914
What check-up? No need.
I'm going home tomorrow.

80
00:05:40,007 --> 00:05:42,791
Go home my ass. You have
to stay two or three more nights.

81
00:05:43,398 --> 00:05:47,411
Direk, you know I hate
staying in the hospital.

82
00:05:47,527 --> 00:05:49,299
Just lie down and stop complaining.

83
00:05:49,527 --> 00:05:51,282
The doctor needs to run a few more tests.

84
00:05:51,428 --> 00:05:53,528
- Got it?
- Forget about it, I'm fine.

85
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:56,816
Please tay here a bit longer.

86
00:05:58,168 --> 00:05:59,168
Okay.

87
00:06:00,011 --> 00:06:03,407
You're so obedient like a puppy.
But with me, you're stubborn as hell.

88
00:06:03,841 --> 00:06:04,214
Tch.

89
00:06:04,629 --> 00:06:05,629
Well then,

90
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,440
I'll leave him in your care, Daotok.

91
00:06:08,632 --> 00:06:10,565
I need to handle something.

92
00:06:11,939 --> 00:06:13,308
And behave yourself.

93
00:06:20,367 --> 00:06:21,367
It hurts.

94
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:23,564
- Here.
- Drink some water.

95
00:06:41,235 --> 00:06:42,235
Hey.

96
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:43,860
What's wrong?

97
00:06:51,016 --> 00:06:52,016
Come here.

98
00:06:52,974 --> 00:06:53,974
Let's talk.

99
00:06:56,831 --> 00:06:57,831
What's wrong?

100
00:06:59,414 --> 00:07:00,917
Why won't you say anything?

101
00:07:01,780 --> 00:07:02,780
Are you mad?

102
00:07:03,881 --> 00:07:04,881
Hmm?

103
00:07:06,355 --> 00:07:08,370
I couldn't do anything at all.

104
00:07:10,014 --> 00:07:13,454
Maybe it's because I've never
been in a situation like this before.

105
00:07:15,562 --> 00:07:17,071
But I was scared.

106
00:07:20,466 --> 00:07:21,838
I was really scared.

107
00:07:26,090 --> 00:07:28,514
I'm not someone who cries easily.

108
00:07:30,662 --> 00:07:32,114
But I still cried.

109
00:07:33,678 --> 00:07:37,029
I've never felt this weak before.

110
00:07:39,177 --> 00:07:40,908
And it's all because of you.

111
00:07:42,463 --> 00:07:44,118
You came out of nowhere,

112
00:07:45,219 --> 00:07:46,751
and walked into my life.

113
00:07:50,048 --> 00:07:51,437
You came to like me,

114
00:07:53,465 --> 00:07:54,731
to care about me,

115
00:07:55,616 --> 00:07:56,831
to look after me,

116
00:07:58,994 --> 00:08:01,659
and then made me worry
about you like I was going crazy.

117
00:08:06,374 --> 00:08:07,374
I'm sorry.

118
00:08:08,703 --> 00:08:11,272
I didn't say that so you'd apologize.

119
00:08:12,931 --> 00:08:14,385
Then what do you want me to do?

120
00:08:16,844 --> 00:08:18,404
Take responsibility.

121
00:08:19,278 --> 00:08:20,702
Responsibility for what?

122
00:08:24,002 --> 00:08:25,002
Be...

123
00:08:28,512 --> 00:08:29,512
Be what?

124
00:08:30,413 --> 00:08:31,774
Don't tease me.

125
00:08:32,456 --> 00:08:33,546
You haven't even asked yet.

126
00:08:34,354 --> 00:08:35,583
I can be anything.

127
00:08:36,355 --> 00:08:38,165
Whatever you want me to be,

128
00:08:38,608 --> 00:08:39,847
I can be all of it.

129
00:08:40,465 --> 00:08:41,465
I mean it.

130
00:08:42,675 --> 00:08:43,675
Go on, ask me.

131
00:08:45,349 --> 00:08:46,349
Anything at all?

132
00:08:47,434 --> 00:08:48,434
Anything.

133
00:08:49,837 --> 00:08:51,730
Be the blue-haired kid next door?

134
00:08:52,525 --> 00:08:53,525
I will.

135
00:08:54,105 --> 00:08:55,765
Be a low-battery robot?

136
00:08:56,888 --> 00:08:57,888
I will.

137
00:08:59,091 --> 00:09:01,103
Be someone who stays by my side,

138
00:09:03,798 --> 00:09:04,977
and never leaves,

139
00:09:06,697 --> 00:09:08,585
no matter what happens?

140
00:09:09,468 --> 00:09:10,468
I will.

141
00:09:11,068 --> 00:09:12,583
Be the one who loves me the most?

142
00:09:13,725 --> 00:09:14,725
I will.

143
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:17,440
Then...

144
00:09:23,211 --> 00:09:24,389
Be my boyfriend.

145
00:09:26,133 --> 00:09:27,133
I will.

146
00:09:29,115 --> 00:09:30,733
Let me be that person.

147
00:09:33,370 --> 00:09:34,370
Please.

148
00:10:06,251 --> 00:10:07,251
Arthit.

149
00:10:07,533 --> 00:10:08,533
Hmm?

150
00:10:09,333 --> 00:10:10,788
Why don't you call me P'?

151
00:10:11,865 --> 00:10:12,865
Hey.

152
00:10:13,068 --> 00:10:14,068
Don't tell me

153
00:10:14,293 --> 00:10:16,001
you don't respect me anymore.

154
00:10:17,497 --> 00:10:19,490
I don't call my boyfriend “P'.”

155
00:10:21,626 --> 00:10:22,678
Shit.

156
00:10:23,810 --> 00:10:25,776
We should get the
hell out of this hospital.

157
00:10:25,872 --> 00:10:27,574
Staying here is pointless now.

158
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:29,000
Wanna leave right now?

159
00:10:29,334 --> 00:10:30,542
Go to sleep.

160
00:10:32,620 --> 00:10:33,620
Then sleep with me.

161
00:10:34,560 --> 00:10:35,560
No.

162
00:10:36,253 --> 00:10:37,737
This is a patient's bed.

163
00:10:38,075 --> 00:10:39,456
So what?

164
00:10:46,522 --> 00:10:47,727
Be a good boy.

165
00:10:48,438 --> 00:10:49,810
Get plenty of rest,

166
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,352
so you'll recover quickly.

167
00:10:58,880 --> 00:10:59,880
Mm.

168
00:10:59,980 --> 00:11:01,105
Goodnight kiss.

169
00:11:13,897 --> 00:11:15,657
I love you more than
anything in this world.

170
00:11:15,734 --> 00:11:17,120
I love you too, Arthit.

171
00:11:17,962 --> 00:11:19,444
You're the best.

172
00:11:33,625 --> 00:11:35,517
You asshole.

173
00:11:35,685 --> 00:11:37,219
I'm trying to sleep.

174
00:11:37,571 --> 00:11:39,734
You wanna die a second time or what?

175
00:11:41,671 --> 00:11:43,001
This idiot.

176
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:20,854
Wake up.

177
00:12:27,198 --> 00:12:28,757
Why are you sleeping here?

178
00:12:31,315 --> 00:12:34,268
Shit, a ghost scared me last night.

179
00:12:35,817 --> 00:12:36,817
Really?

180
00:12:37,084 --> 00:12:37,717
Yeah.

181
00:12:38,008 --> 00:12:39,314
It was terrifying.

182
00:12:39,394 --> 00:12:40,933
So I came to sleep with you here.

183
00:12:43,503 --> 00:12:45,001
But you're not afraid of ghosts.

184
00:12:46,690 --> 00:12:47,690
Oh?

185
00:12:51,330 --> 00:12:53,604
Good morning, my boyfriend.

186
00:13:14,647 --> 00:13:16,414
Hey, Hill!

187
00:13:18,499 --> 00:13:20,213
Wait— Ow, damn it, Hill!

188
00:13:20,311 --> 00:13:22,214
- Yeah.
- Ouch, you jerk.

189
00:13:22,314 --> 00:13:23,314
You'll be fine.

190
00:13:24,291 --> 00:13:25,460
Thanks, maew.

191
00:13:25,921 --> 00:13:27,580
For taking care of K'John.

192
00:13:27,890 --> 00:13:28,890
No problem at all.

193
00:13:32,823 --> 00:13:34,550
Is he asleep or dead?

194
00:13:36,282 --> 00:13:37,282
Rest in peace, my friend.

195
00:13:37,807 --> 00:13:39,346
Shit, North, help me out!

196
00:13:39,419 --> 00:13:40,685
I am helping.

197
00:13:41,091 --> 00:13:42,173
Get in, get in!

198
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:43,442
- Yeah.
- Stunned! Stunned!

199
00:13:43,505 --> 00:13:44,542
Come on, push it in!

200
00:13:46,731 --> 00:13:48,967
Jo, you asshole—that's my get-well gift!

201
00:13:49,198 --> 00:13:51,398
- So you can't even split this with me or what?
- I can.

202
00:13:51,980 --> 00:13:53,518
But you have to feed me too.

203
00:13:54,118 --> 00:13:55,118
Hurry up.

204
00:13:56,164 --> 00:13:57,164
Ouch.

205
00:13:58,810 --> 00:13:59,810
That's enough.

206
00:14:25,845 --> 00:14:27,161
Can I talk to you for a second?

207
00:14:29,616 --> 00:14:30,983
You're already dead.

208
00:14:31,331 --> 00:14:33,499
You can't be hogging the bed like this.

209
00:14:33,877 --> 00:14:35,410
The people lying here

210
00:14:35,551 --> 00:14:36,705
were sick before too.

211
00:14:37,694 --> 00:14:39,896
Why create more bad karma?

212
00:14:42,653 --> 00:14:44,088
I'll make merit for you.

213
00:14:44,663 --> 00:14:48,391
But you have to promise
not to haunt anyone again.

214
00:15:27,290 --> 00:15:27,988
Hey.

215
00:15:28,282 --> 00:15:29,282
Hmm?

216
00:15:30,669 --> 00:15:31,669
Are you going to drive?

217
00:15:31,826 --> 00:15:32,826
Yeah.

218
00:15:33,321 --> 00:15:35,333
Then the patient should just sit still.

219
00:15:41,534 --> 00:15:42,951
Want to go somewhere?

220
00:15:43,640 --> 00:15:45,457
Mm.

221
00:15:47,893 --> 00:15:49,053
I want to go back to my room.

222
00:16:52,385 --> 00:16:53,385
Do you know

223
00:16:53,951 --> 00:16:55,925
how long I've been waiting for this moment?

224
00:16:55,986 --> 00:16:59,902
I also want to see how
prepared you really are.

225
00:17:47,453 --> 00:17:48,971
Just relax.

226
00:17:49,328 --> 00:17:50,558
No need to tense up.

227
00:18:10,783 --> 00:18:12,300
I love you so much.

228
00:19:18,842 --> 00:19:19,946
How are you?

229
00:19:30,650 --> 00:19:31,764
Why are you avoiding me?

230
00:19:33,425 --> 00:19:34,894
Was last night okay?

231
00:19:38,656 --> 00:19:40,022
If I say it wasn't okay?

232
00:19:41,112 --> 00:19:42,835
I'll practice more.

233
00:19:53,296 --> 00:19:54,543
It was good.

234
00:19:55,631 --> 00:19:57,111
Really good, you know?

235
00:19:58,051 --> 00:19:59,951
The best in my life.

236
00:20:02,807 --> 00:20:05,493
And it'll stay this good
for the rest of our lives.

237
00:20:06,814 --> 00:20:07,814
Sweet talker.

238
00:20:11,390 --> 00:20:12,429
Of course I'm sweet.

239
00:20:13,571 --> 00:20:14,597
Want a taste?

240
00:20:32,171 --> 00:20:33,662
Emma, look.

241
00:20:34,152 --> 00:20:35,509
Our son's boyfriend

242
00:20:35,709 --> 00:20:37,434
draws just as well as you.

243
00:20:40,791 --> 00:20:41,791
I'm so proud.

244
00:20:42,340 --> 00:20:45,782
Drawing this beautifully—I
guess you deserve a reward.

245
00:20:47,854 --> 00:20:49,773
- Ouch.
- Don't try to be slick.

246
00:20:51,244 --> 00:20:54,103
So now that you've got a boyfriend,
you're not into anyone else?

247
00:20:54,234 --> 00:20:55,234
Of course, Direk.

248
00:20:56,069 --> 00:20:57,662
If I'm doing anyone, it's my boyfriend.

249
00:20:58,183 --> 00:20:59,183
Ouch.

250
00:21:00,011 --> 00:21:01,011
That hurts.

251
00:21:08,780 --> 00:21:09,780
What's up, Fah?

252
00:21:11,457 --> 00:21:14,093
I've been discharged, but I still hurt.

253
00:21:14,752 --> 00:21:15,899
Can I extend my leave?

254
00:21:16,240 --> 00:21:19,327
My wound can't be seen
from the outside, Fah.

255
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:22,490
But honestly, I'm in really
bad shape, you get me?

256
00:21:23,484 --> 00:21:24,484
Yeah.

257
00:21:25,022 --> 00:21:27,822
If he doesn't like it, I don't know
why he'd put himself through that.

258
00:21:28,751 --> 00:21:30,751
I've told him so many
times, he just won't listen.

259
00:21:31,238 --> 00:21:32,911
Even before the medical exam.

260
00:21:34,065 --> 00:21:36,121
I said "If you don't like
something, don't force it."

261
00:21:36,145 --> 00:21:37,699
"You're only hurting yourself."

262
00:21:40,117 --> 00:21:41,862
But he said he wants to study medicine.

263
00:21:42,117 --> 00:21:43,453
Because of his mom, right?

264
00:21:44,478 --> 00:21:45,478
Yeah.

265
00:21:46,648 --> 00:21:49,115
He promised Emma when she was sick

266
00:21:49,253 --> 00:21:51,191
that he'd become a doctor to treat her.

267
00:21:51,586 --> 00:21:54,000
But I don't see why that's necessary.

268
00:21:54,423 --> 00:21:58,804
Emma herself probably wouldn't
want him enduring something he hates.

269
00:22:00,863 --> 00:22:01,967
That's true.

270
00:22:04,920 --> 00:22:06,754
If it were you saying it,

271
00:22:07,832 --> 00:22:09,110
maybe he'd listen.

272
00:22:14,762 --> 00:22:16,560
Yeah, help me take leave.

273
00:22:17,360 --> 00:22:18,490
I'll give it a try.

274
00:22:29,088 --> 00:22:31,080
The professor will
probably dismiss us late.

275
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:32,485
No need to pick me up.

276
00:22:32,742 --> 00:22:33,976
I'll go back with North.

277
00:22:37,552 --> 00:22:39,745
Tell that North I'll slash his tires.

278
00:22:41,285 --> 00:22:44,108
I'm serious. Don't come pick me up.

279
00:22:44,533 --> 00:22:45,641
Or I'll be mad.

280
00:22:47,681 --> 00:22:48,681
Alright.

281
00:22:52,253 --> 00:22:53,290
Good job.

282
00:22:58,395 --> 00:22:59,515
How much for the cigarettes?

283
00:23:00,777 --> 00:23:01,954
How much for the cigarettes?

284
00:23:06,857 --> 00:23:07,592
A hundred each.

285
00:23:07,850 --> 00:23:09,885
Put it on my tab. The cash is in my room.

286
00:24:55,952 --> 00:24:56,992
Did you write it yourself?

287
00:24:57,564 --> 00:24:58,564
Yeah.

288
00:25:00,348 --> 00:25:01,348
Actually,

289
00:25:01,382 --> 00:25:02,491
I started it a while ago.

290
00:25:02,785 --> 00:25:03,785
But I just finished it.

291
00:25:04,826 --> 00:25:06,208
The song is really good.

292
00:25:07,807 --> 00:25:08,807
You're so talented.

293
00:25:09,419 --> 00:25:10,447
You think so?

294
00:25:10,920 --> 00:25:12,400
You're not just flattering me, right?

295
00:25:12,632 --> 00:25:15,567
Why would I? It really is good.

296
00:25:16,148 --> 00:25:17,148
Mm.

297
00:25:18,210 --> 00:25:19,358
Can I see it?

298
00:25:21,155 --> 00:25:22,155
Sure.

299
00:25:25,525 --> 00:25:27,964
Honestly,

300
00:25:28,950 --> 00:25:31,733
I thought I was just writing
it for fun like the other times.

301
00:25:32,478 --> 00:25:34,120
But when I thought of your face,

302
00:25:34,840 --> 00:25:36,457
I suddenly wanted to take it seriously.

303
00:25:38,571 --> 00:25:40,770
So this song is...

304
00:25:41,614 --> 00:25:42,614
Written for you.

305
00:25:48,105 --> 00:25:49,188
Thank you.

306
00:25:50,245 --> 00:25:51,545
I'm really happy.

307
00:25:52,717 --> 00:25:55,167
You've taken another
step toward your dream.

308
00:25:56,622 --> 00:25:58,841
Then I deserve a kiss
on the cheek as a reward.

309
00:25:59,838 --> 00:26:01,285
That has nothing to do with it.

310
00:26:02,074 --> 00:26:03,074
Just a little.

311
00:26:07,090 --> 00:26:09,078
Are you going to release
it for others to listen?

312
00:26:10,223 --> 00:26:11,223
I don't know.

313
00:26:13,176 --> 00:26:14,531
If I really do it,

314
00:26:14,604 --> 00:26:16,570
I'll need to arrange it better.

315
00:26:17,208 --> 00:26:19,271
And improve the music.

316
00:26:19,860 --> 00:26:20,967
Then record it in a studio.

317
00:26:21,579 --> 00:26:22,579
Mm.

318
00:26:24,302 --> 00:26:26,029
I want Arthit to release it.

319
00:26:27,197 --> 00:26:28,915
I don't want to keep it to myself.

320
00:26:29,722 --> 00:26:30,722
Mm.

321
00:26:32,068 --> 00:26:33,610
Then once I finish it,

322
00:26:35,321 --> 00:26:36,743
I'll let you listen it first.

323
00:26:37,634 --> 00:26:38,634
Okay?

324
00:26:41,573 --> 00:26:42,573
I'll wait.

325
00:26:42,866 --> 00:26:43,866
Mm.

326
00:26:55,948 --> 00:26:58,238
You're quite a spendthrift.

327
00:26:58,924 --> 00:27:00,682
If I earn money, I've got to spend it.

328
00:27:01,474 --> 00:27:02,597
Why save it?

329
00:27:03,505 --> 00:27:05,554
And if one day your savings run out,

330
00:27:06,118 --> 00:27:07,118
what will you do?

331
00:27:07,241 --> 00:27:08,841
That just means I'm not rich enough yet.

332
00:27:09,312 --> 00:27:10,882
Look at my best friend Jo.

333
00:27:11,358 --> 00:27:12,518
He's so rich that his savings

334
00:27:12,672 --> 00:27:14,360
are just the money he hasn't spent.

335
00:27:16,574 --> 00:27:18,226
You're unbelievable, Arthit.

336
00:27:19,549 --> 00:27:21,069
I really love it when you say my name.

337
00:27:25,080 --> 00:27:26,080
Arthit.

338
00:27:26,845 --> 00:27:27,845
Arthit.

339
00:27:28,706 --> 00:27:29,706
Hmm?

340
00:27:30,299 --> 00:27:31,299
Arthit.

341
00:27:34,231 --> 00:27:35,231
Oh.

342
00:27:35,296 --> 00:27:37,282
So, you told your family about us, right?

343
00:27:37,896 --> 00:27:38,896
I did.

344
00:27:41,005 --> 00:27:42,005
What did they say?

345
00:27:43,007 --> 00:27:45,075
Papa and Dad were a little shocked.

346
00:27:45,709 --> 00:27:48,884
Grandma invited us over for dinner.

347
00:27:49,760 --> 00:27:50,760
So, shall we go?

348
00:27:51,417 --> 00:27:53,057
Won't Arthit feel uncomfortable?

349
00:27:53,474 --> 00:27:54,474
Hmm?

350
00:27:54,665 --> 00:27:55,354
Me?

351
00:27:55,660 --> 00:27:56,349
Uncomfortable?

352
00:27:56,595 --> 00:27:57,595
Mm.

353
00:27:58,185 --> 00:28:00,835
Just watch me win your family over.

354
00:28:01,383 --> 00:28:02,383
You'll see.

355
00:28:05,231 --> 00:28:06,528
Then I'll take you there.

356
00:28:12,231 --> 00:28:13,231
Hey.

357
00:28:14,740 --> 00:28:17,315
How did your Papa and Dad meet?

358
00:28:19,389 --> 00:28:21,179
Papa was Dad's love at first sight.

359
00:28:21,571 --> 00:28:23,266
They met at a café in London.

360
00:28:29,758 --> 00:28:31,082
Love at first sight?

361
00:28:32,469 --> 00:28:33,469
Mm.

362
00:28:36,805 --> 00:28:38,035
But.

363
00:28:38,589 --> 00:28:40,602
I guess ours wasn't love at first sight.

364
00:28:41,881 --> 00:28:44,365
It took me quite a while

365
00:28:45,085 --> 00:28:46,588
to start liking you.

366
00:28:48,711 --> 00:28:52,585
I can't even imagine what it'd be like

367
00:28:54,897 --> 00:28:56,105
if you hadn't moved next door.

368
00:28:57,542 --> 00:29:00,072
We would've met some other way anyway.

369
00:29:01,262 --> 00:29:02,262
Hmm?

370
00:29:03,314 --> 00:29:04,314
Why?

371
00:29:05,370 --> 00:29:06,610
I went to see a fortune teller.

372
00:29:08,391 --> 00:29:09,391
Seriously?

373
00:29:09,992 --> 00:29:10,992
Mm.

374
00:29:12,093 --> 00:29:13,474
We're soulmates.

375
00:29:14,943 --> 00:29:16,103
Mm...

376
00:29:16,921 --> 00:29:18,287
So that means

377
00:29:19,560 --> 00:29:21,580
no matter what happens,

378
00:29:22,562 --> 00:29:24,121
we're meant to be together, right?

379
00:29:26,642 --> 00:29:27,642
Mm.

380
00:29:30,030 --> 00:29:31,509
Is that from the fortune teller too?

381
00:29:32,394 --> 00:29:33,394
No, that's from my heart.

382
00:29:35,600 --> 00:29:36,754
Damn.

383
00:29:43,099 --> 00:29:44,786
Keep your eyes on the road.

384
00:29:45,389 --> 00:29:46,514
Drive carefully.

385
00:29:49,357 --> 00:29:50,700
I just want to get home quickly.

386
00:29:59,571 --> 00:30:00,571
Let's go.

387
00:30:08,767 --> 00:30:10,231
Papa, Dad.

388
00:30:10,398 --> 00:30:13,814
Come here. I missed you.

389
00:30:14,477 --> 00:30:17,983
- We missed you. Welcome home.
- I missed you too.

390
00:30:18,365 --> 00:30:19,445
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you.

391
00:30:29,487 --> 00:30:31,598
We haven't seen each other for a bit

392
00:30:31,924 --> 00:30:34,253
why have you put on so much weight, K'John?

393
00:30:34,727 --> 00:30:36,493
That's the one who's been feeding him.

394
00:30:36,712 --> 00:30:40,019
Seems like he's feeding my kid too?

395
00:30:41,826 --> 00:30:44,297
Your cheeks are so chubby!

396
00:30:46,020 --> 00:30:48,342
Ok, let's go inside. Granny's waiting.

397
00:30:48,970 --> 00:30:49,970
Let's go inside.

398
00:30:50,011 --> 00:30:51,011
Let's go.

399
00:31:01,851 --> 00:31:02,862
Excuse me for a moment.

400
00:31:02,970 --> 00:31:03,970
Oh?

401
00:31:04,441 --> 00:31:05,441
Where's my grandson?

402
00:31:07,423 --> 00:31:08,939
Khun Phuangthong.

403
00:31:09,115 --> 00:31:14,170
How are you, my grandson?
I'm so happy to see you.

404
00:31:14,308 --> 00:31:16,136
I've missed you so much, Khun Phuangthong.

405
00:31:16,241 --> 00:31:17,779
I've missed you too.

406
00:31:21,515 --> 00:31:22,025
Oh.

407
00:31:22,121 --> 00:31:22,565
Ah.

408
00:31:23,145 --> 00:31:24,145
Come sit down.

409
00:31:26,134 --> 00:31:27,134
Yes, ma'am.

410
00:31:32,642 --> 00:31:33,918
So handsome.

411
00:31:34,364 --> 00:31:36,204
Both son and grandson.

412
00:31:36,506 --> 00:31:40,534
You really know how to find a
son-in-law and a grandson-in-law I like.

413
00:31:41,413 --> 00:31:43,629
I'll go help Papa in the kitchen first.

414
00:31:44,493 --> 00:31:45,238
Alright, alright.

415
00:31:45,466 --> 00:31:46,654
Go ahead and talk.

416
00:31:46,712 --> 00:31:47,712
Okay.

417
00:31:51,776 --> 00:31:53,065
What's your name?

418
00:31:53,299 --> 00:31:54,429
My name is Arthit.

419
00:31:54,908 --> 00:31:57,197
Hmm, that's a lovely name.

420
00:31:58,435 --> 00:31:59,982
And what's your name?

421
00:32:00,201 --> 00:32:02,114
Phuangthong.

422
00:32:02,253 --> 00:32:04,635
Hmm, that's a lovely name.

423
00:32:06,047 --> 00:32:07,047
This young man…

424
00:32:07,539 --> 00:32:08,539
Not bad at all.

425
00:32:13,022 --> 00:32:14,751
Here, let me help.

426
00:32:15,136 --> 00:32:16,248
It's okay.

427
00:32:18,189 --> 00:32:19,906
Grandma seems to like him.

428
00:32:20,149 --> 00:32:21,748
They seem to get along well.

429
00:32:22,688 --> 00:32:23,688
Seems like it.

430
00:32:25,617 --> 00:32:27,813
Aren't Papa and Dad going to work today?

431
00:32:28,114 --> 00:32:29,183
No.

432
00:32:29,514 --> 00:32:30,844
We knew you were coming.

433
00:32:31,482 --> 00:32:33,035
I took leave in advance.

434
00:32:33,549 --> 00:32:34,549
Oh.

435
00:32:37,952 --> 00:32:38,952
Papa.

436
00:32:41,502 --> 00:32:42,514
Are you okay with this?

437
00:32:45,934 --> 00:32:47,097
I am.

438
00:32:49,720 --> 00:32:51,680
I respect your decision.

439
00:32:52,351 --> 00:32:53,351
But.

440
00:32:54,208 --> 00:32:55,974
I don't know him well enough yet.

441
00:32:56,394 --> 00:32:58,850
So let me keep an eye on him first.

442
00:32:59,391 --> 00:33:00,391
Sure.

443
00:33:01,543 --> 00:33:02,543
My grandson…

444
00:33:02,891 --> 00:33:04,651
He's been a quiet
child since he was little.

445
00:33:05,150 --> 00:33:09,826
Back in kindergarten, the teacher
wrote that he wasn't cheerful.

446
00:33:09,859 --> 00:33:11,920
Not very sociable.

447
00:33:12,542 --> 00:33:13,248
Mm.

448
00:33:13,352 --> 00:33:17,120
They even called in his guardian,
worried there might be family problems.

449
00:33:18,420 --> 00:33:20,022
Even now, he doesn't talk much.

450
00:33:21,271 --> 00:33:23,400
Back then, whenever I asked him something…

451
00:33:23,705 --> 00:33:24,705
He'd just reply...

452
00:33:24,845 --> 00:33:25,528
Mm.

453
00:33:25,829 --> 00:33:26,829
Mm-hmm.

454
00:33:28,557 --> 00:33:31,471
Honestly, we could barely have
a proper conversation, Grandma.

455
00:33:34,220 --> 00:33:35,220
Ma'am.

456
00:33:35,696 --> 00:33:39,321
No need to be formal.
Just speak the way you normally do.

457
00:33:39,690 --> 00:33:41,771
- Like how I usually talk…
- Mm.

458
00:33:42,619 --> 00:33:44,134
Can you handle that?

459
00:33:44,229 --> 00:33:46,400
I can.

460
00:33:46,857 --> 00:33:50,145
Just don't speak English like Gavin.

461
00:33:50,223 --> 00:33:51,801
I can't understand a word.

462
00:33:54,081 --> 00:33:55,635
At first, when Phai

463
00:33:56,740 --> 00:33:59,401
was introduced to me, I was so stressed.

464
00:33:59,425 --> 00:34:01,026
- Mm.
- It's not that I didn't like him.

465
00:34:01,170 --> 00:34:05,346
But he kept saying things I didn't
understand. What if he was badmouthing me?

466
00:34:05,500 --> 00:34:07,056
- Oh.
- Even now,

467
00:34:07,717 --> 00:34:11,447
It's still so hard to talk to him.

468
00:34:11,740 --> 00:34:15,220
All I can say is “Hey, hey, come on.”

469
00:34:19,234 --> 00:34:21,614
So how did you end up liking my grandson?

470
00:34:23,425 --> 00:34:24,533
I'm not sure.

471
00:34:25,493 --> 00:34:27,088
After spending some time together,

472
00:34:27,293 --> 00:34:28,893
I just started liking Dao for being Dao.

473
00:34:30,936 --> 00:34:31,976
I can't really explain it.

474
00:34:32,613 --> 00:34:33,613
I see.

475
00:34:33,884 --> 00:34:35,868
What about at university?
Does he have friends?

476
00:34:36,125 --> 00:34:37,125
He does.

477
00:34:37,792 --> 00:34:39,226
They seem pretty close.

478
00:34:39,669 --> 00:34:41,247
They're all nice guys.

479
00:34:41,779 --> 00:34:42,779
Although…

480
00:34:43,475 --> 00:34:45,370
Some of them can be a bit cheeky.

481
00:34:47,327 --> 00:34:50,432
Why? Were you worried
Dao wouldn't have friends?

482
00:34:51,478 --> 00:34:52,958
Of course I was.

483
00:34:53,207 --> 00:34:54,402
I don't know why, but…

484
00:34:54,798 --> 00:34:55,952
Daotok...

485
00:34:56,278 --> 00:34:58,755
He always seems to attract bad people.

486
00:34:59,192 --> 00:35:00,518
Oh.

487
00:35:00,776 --> 00:35:02,125
But hearing this,

488
00:35:02,859 --> 00:35:04,091
I feel relieved.

489
00:35:04,628 --> 00:35:07,813
With you taking care of him,
I'm not worried anymore.

490
00:35:11,357 --> 00:35:15,490
I won't say I'm a good person, but
when it comes to taking care of Daotok.

491
00:35:16,025 --> 00:35:19,583
I promise I'll do my very best.

492
00:35:21,601 --> 00:35:22,601
I promise.

493
00:35:29,693 --> 00:35:30,920
The room's a bit small.

494
00:35:31,154 --> 00:35:32,265
Can you sleep here?

495
00:35:33,522 --> 00:35:34,522
Small?

496
00:35:35,182 --> 00:35:36,742
I've slept in tighter spaces than this.

497
00:35:44,682 --> 00:35:45,682
Hey.

498
00:35:47,037 --> 00:35:48,197
Are you being clingy with me?

499
00:35:48,989 --> 00:35:50,800
We haven't hugged today yet.

500
00:35:58,662 --> 00:36:00,157
What's gotten into you, huh?

501
00:36:01,275 --> 00:36:02,275
Well.

502
00:36:02,718 --> 00:36:03,718
I kinda want a hug.

503
00:36:06,416 --> 00:36:07,416
Dad's here.

504
00:36:08,943 --> 00:36:10,367
Wanna go play soccer?

505
00:36:11,077 --> 00:36:12,077
Sure.

506
00:36:12,487 --> 00:36:13,487
Let's go.

507
00:36:16,702 --> 00:36:17,952
Go. Move you legs.

508
00:36:19,389 --> 00:36:21,991
Okay, okay, spread out!

509
00:36:22,081 --> 00:36:23,081
Nice one!

510
00:36:25,829 --> 00:36:26,829
Okay.

511
00:36:28,918 --> 00:36:30,922
Goal!

512
00:36:35,677 --> 00:36:36,677
Not bad.

513
00:36:37,148 --> 00:36:39,945
No wonder you're the captain
of the Med School football team.

514
00:36:40,671 --> 00:36:41,671
You're good too.

515
00:36:42,447 --> 00:36:44,297
But you are not on my level yet.

516
00:36:44,697 --> 00:36:46,958
Damn, I really like this guy.

517
00:36:47,527 --> 00:36:51,044
But there's no way I'm
losing in front of Phai.

518
00:36:56,872 --> 00:36:57,872
Me too.

519
00:36:59,025 --> 00:37:01,034
I can't lose in front of Dao.

520
00:37:01,438 --> 00:37:02,438
Let's do it.

521
00:37:02,499 --> 00:37:03,499
Let's go.

522
00:37:07,530 --> 00:37:09,090
The food is really good tonight.

523
00:37:09,244 --> 00:37:10,968
- Yeah.
- I'm so full.

524
00:37:15,288 --> 00:37:16,408
This is really good whiskey.

525
00:37:26,026 --> 00:37:27,259
Uh...

526
00:37:28,465 --> 00:37:29,465
Can I join?

527
00:37:35,795 --> 00:37:37,404
What's up? Can't sleep?

528
00:37:38,115 --> 00:37:39,208
Uh.

529
00:37:40,010 --> 00:37:41,211
I just...

530
00:37:42,231 --> 00:37:44,294
Oh, never mind. Make yourself at home.

531
00:37:45,191 --> 00:37:46,191
Oh.

532
00:37:47,062 --> 00:37:48,062
So...

533
00:37:49,149 --> 00:37:50,685
You...

534
00:37:50,977 --> 00:37:52,727
You can just call me like Daotok.

535
00:37:53,001 --> 00:37:54,001
Oh.

536
00:37:54,804 --> 00:37:55,614
Yes, Papa.

537
00:37:55,811 --> 00:37:57,694
Hey, no need to be so formal.

538
00:37:58,899 --> 00:37:59,899
Okay.

539
00:38:01,798 --> 00:38:03,085
Oh, thank you.

540
00:38:03,213 --> 00:38:04,597
Cheers.

541
00:38:10,642 --> 00:38:13,309
Hey, I don't doubt you and Daotok.

542
00:38:13,909 --> 00:38:16,118
I'm just a little worried.

543
00:38:16,325 --> 00:38:18,845
He's my only son.

544
00:38:18,992 --> 00:38:23,327
I want him to meet
someone who truly loves him.

545
00:38:23,671 --> 00:38:25,688
And that person is you.

546
00:38:26,840 --> 00:38:28,392
Thank you so much.

547
00:38:28,668 --> 00:38:32,287
I haven't seen him this
happy in a long time.

548
00:38:32,802 --> 00:38:35,019
No need to thank me.

549
00:38:35,469 --> 00:38:36,994
As long as Dao is happy,

550
00:38:38,223 --> 00:38:40,792
I'm damn happy too.

551
00:38:47,557 --> 00:38:49,521
Phai, that's enough.

552
00:38:54,525 --> 00:38:55,525
Dylan.

553
00:38:55,703 --> 00:38:56,703
Hmm?

554
00:38:57,168 --> 00:38:59,877
If you make my son cry,

555
00:39:00,263 --> 00:39:01,911
I'll kill you.

556
00:39:03,023 --> 00:39:04,023
You got it?

557
00:39:04,146 --> 00:39:05,151
Yes.

558
00:39:06,251 --> 00:39:07,251
Gawin.

559
00:39:07,480 --> 00:39:08,703
You have to deal with him

560
00:39:09,054 --> 00:39:10,971
if he hurts Dao.

561
00:39:11,345 --> 00:39:12,345
I got it.

562
00:39:13,567 --> 00:39:14,162
Kid.

563
00:39:14,485 --> 00:39:14,874
Hmm?

564
00:39:14,958 --> 00:39:20,640
If you ever hurt my son even a little,

565
00:39:21,282 --> 00:39:23,389
I won't let you off.

566
00:39:29,154 --> 00:39:31,453
If I ever hurt Dao,

567
00:39:31,877 --> 00:39:33,597
you can kill me.

568
00:39:35,863 --> 00:39:38,165
That's a promise.

569
00:39:39,691 --> 00:39:41,198
On my life.

570
00:39:44,208 --> 00:39:45,850
Cheers.

571
00:40:13,487 --> 00:40:14,508
You smell like alcohol.

572
00:40:15,285 --> 00:40:17,105
I don't.

573
00:40:23,460 --> 00:40:28,266
- Why are you arguing with me?
- What's that?

574
00:40:32,893 --> 00:40:36,826
Is it that funny?

575
00:40:38,262 --> 00:40:39,262
It kind of is.

576
00:40:41,669 --> 00:40:42,825
But it's cute.

577
00:40:51,226 --> 00:40:53,240
You're the only one

578
00:40:55,272 --> 00:40:57,314
who says I'm cute.

579
00:40:59,995 --> 00:41:02,807
Well, you're cute only with me.

580
00:41:03,524 --> 00:41:05,130
Mm.

581
00:41:26,908 --> 00:41:30,060
Don't worry. Papa will
take good care of K'John.

582
00:41:30,955 --> 00:41:33,817
Or should I take K'John
to San Fran with me?

583
00:41:33,951 --> 00:41:35,244
No way.

584
00:41:35,429 --> 00:41:40,053
I'll keep K'John here so you two
will come back to visit us often.

585
00:41:40,474 --> 00:41:41,474
Exactly.

586
00:41:47,685 --> 00:41:48,758
Dad.

587
00:41:49,211 --> 00:41:51,967
- Take care of yourself, son.
- Thank you. See you.

588
00:41:53,096 --> 00:41:55,173
Grandma.

589
00:41:55,297 --> 00:41:57,382
Please take good care of yourself.

590
00:41:57,484 --> 00:41:59,229
You too.

591
00:42:00,853 --> 00:42:04,342
- Young man, take good care of my grandson.
- Of course, Grandma.

592
00:42:04,900 --> 00:42:06,573
I'll take the best care of him.

593
00:42:06,828 --> 00:42:07,828
Don't worry.

594
00:42:26,952 --> 00:42:28,192
We're heading out now. Goodbye.

595
00:42:28,398 --> 00:42:29,398
Goodbye.

596
00:42:30,287 --> 00:42:31,515
- Drive safe.
- Yes.

597
00:42:31,754 --> 00:42:33,911
- Have a safe trip.
- Yes.

598
00:42:57,555 --> 00:42:58,555
Hey.

599
00:44:05,500 --> 00:44:06,780
Is this your completed track?

600
00:44:07,361 --> 00:44:08,361
Mm.

601
00:44:08,814 --> 00:44:09,814
How is it?

602
00:44:11,302 --> 00:44:12,302
It's nice.

603
00:44:12,974 --> 00:44:14,260
It's really nice.

604
00:44:19,262 --> 00:44:19,760
Hey!

605
00:44:20,133 --> 00:44:22,715
But I haven't named the song yet.

606
00:44:23,758 --> 00:44:24,912
Help me think of one.

607
00:44:28,620 --> 00:44:30,142
I like the part...

608
00:44:35,451 --> 00:44:36,451
That one.

609
00:44:37,177 --> 00:44:38,745
On My Shoulder.

610
00:44:39,808 --> 00:44:40,808
Hey!

611
00:44:40,950 --> 00:44:42,078
Alright, I'll use that.

612
00:44:42,334 --> 00:44:43,834
You can't just go with my idea.

613
00:44:44,262 --> 00:44:46,533
- Athit made it.
- Hey.

614
00:44:46,903 --> 00:44:48,117
I made it for you.

615
00:44:53,794 --> 00:44:54,794
Thank you.

616
00:45:04,842 --> 00:45:05,842
So...

617
00:45:06,567 --> 00:45:07,567
If you like it,

618
00:45:07,844 --> 00:45:08,844
I'll post it then.

619
00:45:09,022 --> 00:45:11,494
Make sure you tell all
your friends to share it.

620
00:45:11,773 --> 00:45:12,779
Holy shit, this is crazy.

621
00:45:13,531 --> 00:45:15,522
No way, I'm gonna be famous.

622
00:45:18,342 --> 00:45:21,164
Fah. Jo. Hill.

623
00:45:34,211 --> 00:45:35,299
Holy shit!

624
00:45:35,820 --> 00:45:37,300
It's over a hundred thousand already!

625
00:45:37,840 --> 00:45:38,997
P' Thit is insane.

626
00:45:39,825 --> 00:45:40,825
Can I see?

627
00:45:40,960 --> 00:45:42,105
Here, look.

628
00:45:46,311 --> 00:45:49,183
Hey, but Dao looks
really cute in the video.

629
00:45:50,380 --> 00:45:52,014
P' Athit is pretty talented too.

630
00:45:52,813 --> 00:45:54,602
He compliments himself like that every day.

631
00:45:55,690 --> 00:45:57,624
Seriously, he leaves no room
for anyone else to praise him.

632
00:45:57,648 --> 00:45:59,407
But honestly, the song is really good.

633
00:45:59,758 --> 00:46:02,771
Honestly, at first glance,
P' Athit does look kinda cool.

634
00:46:03,305 --> 00:46:05,277
- But don't get to know the real him.
- Why?

635
00:46:05,576 --> 00:46:06,755
Because he's an asshole.

636
00:46:08,777 --> 00:46:09,777
You jerk.

637
00:46:15,361 --> 00:46:17,511
Hey, have your boyfriends replied yet?

638
00:46:17,739 --> 00:46:18,739
Not yet.

639
00:46:20,537 --> 00:46:21,594
P' Jo hasn't either.

640
00:46:24,394 --> 00:46:26,314
Having boyfriends who
are friends is kinda nice.

641
00:46:26,524 --> 00:46:28,816
When they're busy, they disappear together.

642
00:46:28,927 --> 00:46:31,642
Exactly. That's why we
hang out here so often.

643
00:46:31,970 --> 00:46:34,139
True. No one's as free as us.

644
00:46:34,540 --> 00:46:35,765
We're freaking awesome.

645
00:46:35,802 --> 00:46:36,974
Alright then.

646
00:46:37,179 --> 00:46:39,273
Let's close the book and
play a game instead. Come on.

647
00:46:39,297 --> 00:46:41,417
Whoa, North, what does
that have to do with anything?

648
00:46:41,917 --> 00:46:44,293
You're seriously pointless all day long.

649
00:46:46,112 --> 00:46:47,112
Hey.

650
00:46:49,576 --> 00:46:52,274
What are you doing? I miss you.

651
00:46:58,180 --> 00:46:59,180
Arthit.

652
00:46:59,834 --> 00:47:00,834
Yeah?

653
00:47:01,050 --> 00:47:03,404
I just found out you make
really beautiful music.

654
00:47:04,438 --> 00:47:05,167
Thank you.

655
00:47:05,296 --> 00:47:07,192
Is the person in the
picture your boyfriend?

656
00:47:07,588 --> 00:47:08,588
Yes.

657
00:47:08,697 --> 00:47:09,266
Is he cute?

658
00:47:09,451 --> 00:47:11,925
Of course he is. Are you
showing him off on purpose?

659
00:47:12,456 --> 00:47:13,601
Yeah, I am.

660
00:47:13,786 --> 00:47:14,786
I totally am.

661
00:47:15,240 --> 00:47:19,250
Oh my, I'd better get his autograph
now before he gets even more famous.

662
00:47:21,422 --> 00:47:22,733
I'm heading off.

663
00:47:22,857 --> 00:47:23,857
See you.

664
00:47:24,964 --> 00:47:25,964
So damn smug.

665
00:47:27,825 --> 00:47:30,094
Your boyfriend isn't as cute as mine.

666
00:47:30,687 --> 00:47:32,327
He's only cute for me, and that's enough.

667
00:47:33,042 --> 00:47:34,136
Hey, hold on.

668
00:47:34,616 --> 00:47:35,936
Have you guys shared my song yet?

669
00:47:36,103 --> 00:47:37,103
Of course we did.

670
00:47:37,583 --> 00:47:38,583
Well...

671
00:47:38,951 --> 00:47:39,951
It's pretty good.

672
00:47:40,801 --> 00:47:42,568
I don't know. I don't really listen to music.

673
00:47:42,592 --> 00:47:45,432
But I heard North playing it all day.
He can probably sing along by now.

674
00:47:46,768 --> 00:47:49,613
North is the cutest, seriously.

675
00:47:49,814 --> 00:47:50,814
Jo.

676
00:47:50,957 --> 00:47:52,539
Your boyfriend has great taste.

677
00:47:54,964 --> 00:47:57,820
Hey Hill, has Ter listened to it yet?

678
00:47:58,666 --> 00:48:00,960
What about you? Has Phoon listened?

679
00:48:01,514 --> 00:48:02,514
He has.

680
00:48:26,533 --> 00:48:27,660
Wake up.

681
00:48:28,482 --> 00:48:29,482
Mm?

682
00:48:29,554 --> 00:48:30,733
Wake up.

683
00:48:31,287 --> 00:48:32,287
Mm.

684
00:48:33,008 --> 00:48:34,677
You'll be late for rounds.

685
00:48:35,619 --> 00:48:36,619
Mm.

686
00:49:03,013 --> 00:49:04,013
Arthit.

687
00:49:04,927 --> 00:49:05,927
Mm?

688
00:49:06,749 --> 00:49:07,749
Are you tired?

689
00:49:10,162 --> 00:49:11,162
Why?

690
00:49:12,567 --> 00:49:14,943
Your dad and I once talked about

691
00:49:15,659 --> 00:49:18,333
wanting you to do what you truly love

692
00:49:19,066 --> 00:49:21,448
and live your life happily.

693
00:49:22,242 --> 00:49:23,242
Why?

694
00:49:23,720 --> 00:49:25,522
Why are you being so
serious all of a sudden?

695
00:49:26,922 --> 00:49:28,194
Mm.

696
00:49:28,872 --> 00:49:32,168
I don't want to interfere
with your decision,

697
00:49:33,851 --> 00:49:34,851
but

698
00:49:34,945 --> 00:49:37,635
can I share my opinion?

699
00:49:38,413 --> 00:49:39,413
Mm.

700
00:49:39,854 --> 00:49:41,771
I know that Arthit…

701
00:49:42,274 --> 00:49:43,368
Is someone capable.

702
00:49:45,145 --> 00:49:47,208
Whatever you set your mind to,

703
00:49:47,752 --> 00:49:50,117
it always turns out well.

704
00:49:50,795 --> 00:49:52,229
Even something difficult

705
00:49:52,700 --> 00:49:53,869
like studying medicine.

706
00:49:54,677 --> 00:49:55,677
But…

707
00:49:56,256 --> 00:49:58,634
You're not happy with it at all, are you?

708
00:50:01,551 --> 00:50:06,042
The only thing holding you back right now is
the promise to become a doctor for your mom.

709
00:50:07,687 --> 00:50:09,008
I understand.

710
00:50:09,720 --> 00:50:12,666
Your mom is someone important in your life.

711
00:50:14,505 --> 00:50:15,782
But if she were still here,

712
00:50:17,102 --> 00:50:19,560
would she really want
you to live like this?

713
00:50:22,146 --> 00:50:23,176
I'm saying this

714
00:50:23,530 --> 00:50:26,205
because when I see
you doing what you love

715
00:50:26,706 --> 00:50:28,977
whether it's playing music

716
00:50:29,462 --> 00:50:30,665
or making songs.

717
00:50:31,650 --> 00:50:34,125
I see your eyes light up.

718
00:50:35,011 --> 00:50:37,408
You're really happy doing it, aren't you?

719
00:50:41,680 --> 00:50:43,971
Didn't your dad once say

720
00:50:44,730 --> 00:50:46,502
that if you wanted to make music,

721
00:50:47,260 --> 00:50:49,568
he'd even open a music label for you?

722
00:50:50,351 --> 00:50:51,351
See?

723
00:50:52,426 --> 00:50:54,743
There are so many
people ready to support you.

724
00:50:56,468 --> 00:50:57,468
Mm.

725
00:51:09,600 --> 00:51:10,917
Actually

726
00:51:12,514 --> 00:51:14,642
I've been thinking
about quitting for a while.

727
00:51:15,660 --> 00:51:16,660
I don't know…

728
00:51:17,210 --> 00:51:18,877
Maybe before,

729
00:51:19,610 --> 00:51:21,442
I never really thought about my future.

730
00:51:22,552 --> 00:51:23,863
Whatever happened, happened.

731
00:51:25,865 --> 00:51:27,647
But I'm not like that anymore.

732
00:51:30,180 --> 00:51:31,657
My future…

733
00:51:32,642 --> 00:51:34,564
It's not just about me anymore.

734
00:51:38,088 --> 00:51:39,568
So.

735
00:51:43,570 --> 00:51:45,694
I'll try to live more seriously from now on.

736
00:51:47,583 --> 00:51:49,651
Whatever you decide to do,

737
00:51:50,351 --> 00:51:51,469
whichever path you choose,

738
00:51:53,472 --> 00:51:54,872
I'll be right here.

739
00:52:17,093 --> 00:52:20,983
Hill said you were on sick leave. I thought
you were dying in your room or something.

740
00:52:22,511 --> 00:52:24,635
But you look totally fine.

741
00:52:24,936 --> 00:52:26,048
You're not even sick.

742
00:52:26,287 --> 00:52:27,365
Why'd you take leave then?

743
00:52:34,068 --> 00:52:35,068
Where's North?

744
00:52:36,471 --> 00:52:37,471
Morning class.

745
00:52:42,785 --> 00:52:43,785
You go first.

746
00:52:47,752 --> 00:52:48,937
You know, right,

747
00:52:49,705 --> 00:52:50,813
that I already have a job.

748
00:52:52,256 --> 00:52:53,594
But I studied medicine because

749
00:52:53,743 --> 00:52:54,869
Jean wanted me to.

750
00:52:55,377 --> 00:52:57,591
Though she probably didn't
expect much from me anyway.

751
00:52:57,820 --> 00:53:01,776
Damn, Jo, look.
I've got goosebumps, man.

752
00:53:02,536 --> 00:53:04,543
We're thinking the exact same thing.

753
00:53:05,330 --> 00:53:06,330
You too?

754
00:53:06,533 --> 00:53:07,516
Yeah.

755
00:53:07,540 --> 00:53:08,600
Damn.

756
00:53:09,287 --> 00:53:10,714
Now that we're at this point,

757
00:53:11,555 --> 00:53:13,444
I'm starting to feel like this isn't it.

758
00:53:14,000 --> 00:53:15,960
And this is such a big turning point.

759
00:53:16,413 --> 00:53:17,773
I really need to think it through.

760
00:53:18,167 --> 00:53:20,228
But overthinking isn't really my thing.

761
00:53:21,819 --> 00:53:22,819
So…

762
00:53:23,242 --> 00:53:24,754
Why are you still studying here?

763
00:53:26,690 --> 00:53:28,444
I made a promise to my mom

764
00:53:29,681 --> 00:53:30,681
when I was a kid.

765
00:53:31,561 --> 00:53:33,320
But thinking about it now, Jo,

766
00:53:34,337 --> 00:53:36,428
I don't think she'd want me

767
00:53:36,948 --> 00:53:38,106
to force myself like this.

768
00:53:39,725 --> 00:53:41,605
She'd probably rather see me happy.

769
00:53:43,407 --> 00:53:44,407
So what now?

770
00:53:44,549 --> 00:53:45,549
Should we just quit?

771
00:53:47,183 --> 00:53:48,613
What about Fah and Hill?

772
00:53:49,462 --> 00:53:50,471
Are we just leaving them?

773
00:53:52,530 --> 00:53:54,410
But if we quit, they
might actually be happier.

774
00:53:54,770 --> 00:53:56,116
They won't have to work for us anymore.

775
00:53:56,140 --> 00:53:56,961
They'll be free.

776
00:53:57,100 --> 00:53:58,251
You've got a point.

777
00:53:59,733 --> 00:54:01,801
But I bet they'd still feel a little sad.

778
00:54:07,967 --> 00:54:10,266
I'm free now!

779
00:54:12,063 --> 00:54:13,200
Wait, you quit already?

780
00:54:14,186 --> 00:54:15,186
Huh?

781
00:54:15,287 --> 00:54:16,287
Seriously?

782
00:54:16,702 --> 00:54:17,702
Yeah.

783
00:54:17,942 --> 00:54:20,062
Jo and I just submitted our
resignation a moment ago.

784
00:54:21,179 --> 00:54:23,805
So you guys have really decided, huh?

785
00:54:24,164 --> 00:54:24,694
Mm.

786
00:54:25,174 --> 00:54:25,694
Okay.

787
00:54:26,122 --> 00:54:28,528
Then good luck with the path you've chosen.

788
00:54:28,706 --> 00:54:30,771
Damn, why do you sound so bitter?

789
00:54:31,980 --> 00:54:34,816
You're gonna be lonely without me, huh?

790
00:54:34,964 --> 00:54:37,204
How did you know?

791
00:54:38,031 --> 00:54:41,432
So now Hill and I are
gonna have it way too easy?

792
00:54:42,097 --> 00:54:44,856
Exactly. We can finally
get rid of freeloaders.

793
00:54:45,106 --> 00:54:46,106
Hey!

794
00:54:46,217 --> 00:54:47,674
We did all the work for you

795
00:54:48,213 --> 00:54:52,319
attended classes for you, took notes
for you, took exams on your behalf even.

796
00:54:52,343 --> 00:54:53,822
Damn!

797
00:54:54,020 --> 00:54:56,191
Can you at least pretend to look sad?

798
00:54:57,096 --> 00:54:59,882
Don't look like you've just
been set free or something.

799
00:55:00,851 --> 00:55:02,527
We really do feel that way.

800
00:55:16,124 --> 00:55:16,848
Hey, Thit.

801
00:55:17,118 --> 00:55:18,145
Go home.

802
00:55:18,611 --> 00:55:20,749
What the hell? Why are you kicking me out?

803
00:55:20,983 --> 00:55:22,254
You're annoying.

804
00:55:24,694 --> 00:55:26,574
Hill, turn around and look at this.

805
00:55:27,010 --> 00:55:29,290
- I can do it one-handed, you know.
- I don't want to see.

806
00:55:31,134 --> 00:55:31,656
Jo.

807
00:55:32,155 --> 00:55:32,820
You up for it?

808
00:55:33,127 --> 00:55:34,405
You and me. One-on-one.

809
00:55:34,880 --> 00:55:35,880
Nah.

810
00:55:35,998 --> 00:55:37,558
I'll even give you a one-hand handicap.

811
00:55:39,736 --> 00:55:43,438
Jo, don't be stupid and go along with him.
I already have a headache as it is.

812
00:55:45,192 --> 00:55:46,364
Pathetic.

813
00:55:46,671 --> 00:55:49,974
- Bring it, Thit. No need for the one-hand thing.
- Then come on.

814
00:55:50,251 --> 00:55:50,838
Come on.

815
00:55:51,167 --> 00:55:53,477
I'm ready. Let's go.

816
00:55:53,640 --> 00:55:54,640
Come on.

817
00:56:07,410 --> 00:56:08,653
Your playlist's pretty good.

818
00:56:14,041 --> 00:56:15,240
You like this artist?

819
00:56:17,354 --> 00:56:18,354
I love him.

820
00:56:33,828 --> 00:56:35,638
But I heard he already has a boyfriend.

821
00:56:36,691 --> 00:56:37,786
And he's very much in love.

822
00:56:41,440 --> 00:56:42,845
Then try not to love him.

823
00:56:51,945 --> 00:56:54,195
Hi, Mom. I brought you someone.

824
00:56:54,914 --> 00:56:56,266
This is my boyfriend.

825
00:56:57,168 --> 00:56:58,168
Daotok.

826
00:56:58,358 --> 00:56:59,902
You might be shocked like Direk.

827
00:57:01,205 --> 00:57:02,512
I can see your face now.

828
00:57:04,281 --> 00:57:05,600
You always said

829
00:57:05,976 --> 00:57:07,114
to choose what I love.

830
00:57:08,115 --> 00:57:09,708
So, I did.

831
00:57:10,490 --> 00:57:11,641
I'm happy now.

832
00:57:12,610 --> 00:57:13,610
Just…

833
00:57:15,880 --> 00:57:17,048
Wish you were here.

834
00:57:25,094 --> 00:57:26,191
I miss you.

835
00:57:26,520 --> 00:57:27,520
Mom.

836
00:57:28,517 --> 00:57:29,517
So much.

837
00:57:41,965 --> 00:57:43,708
Can I talk to your mom?

838
00:57:45,491 --> 00:57:46,491
Mm.

839
00:57:50,533 --> 00:57:51,533
Hello, Mom.

840
00:57:52,675 --> 00:57:55,185
I came here to see you a few month ago.

841
00:57:58,220 --> 00:57:59,253
He seem tough,

842
00:58:00,693 --> 00:58:02,890
and stubborn, I guess.

843
00:58:04,354 --> 00:58:05,354
But

844
00:58:06,062 --> 00:58:07,315
he's so honest

845
00:58:08,564 --> 00:58:09,607
and kind.

846
00:58:11,740 --> 00:58:13,699
Especially he has a good heart.

847
00:58:15,568 --> 00:58:16,568
So.

848
00:58:18,614 --> 00:58:20,820
This is the reason why I love him.

849
00:58:22,174 --> 00:58:24,557
No matter what's happen

850
00:58:24,862 --> 00:58:26,035
from now on,

851
00:58:26,845 --> 00:58:28,379
I promise.

852
00:58:30,671 --> 00:58:32,431
I'll be by his side.

853
00:58:36,911 --> 00:58:38,758
And don't worry about him.

854
00:58:40,558 --> 00:58:41,613
And take a rest.

855
00:59:05,902 --> 00:59:07,040
Direk…

856
00:59:08,244 --> 00:59:09,997
Do you think mom would be proud of me?

857
00:59:11,660 --> 00:59:12,942
I really want to know.

858
00:59:14,573 --> 00:59:16,343
But she's not here for me to ask anymore.

859
00:59:22,029 --> 00:59:23,555
If you want my answer,

860
00:59:24,071 --> 00:59:27,100
from over ten years of
being Emma's husband,

861
00:59:27,820 --> 00:59:30,010
I'm sure she's proud of you.

862
00:59:31,035 --> 00:59:32,035
So am I.

863
00:59:33,207 --> 00:59:35,072
You're proud of me?

864
00:59:36,800 --> 00:59:39,561
From the day you were born until today,

865
00:59:40,416 --> 00:59:42,881
there hasn't been a single
day I wasn't proud of you.

866
00:59:43,773 --> 00:59:46,312
I want you to know that

867
00:59:46,982 --> 00:59:48,810
you're the only thing

868
00:59:49,367 --> 00:59:51,671
that's kept me alive all these years.

869
00:59:56,082 --> 00:59:59,423
Damn, I'm gonna cry, Direk.

870
01:00:05,665 --> 01:00:06,665
Thit.

871
01:00:08,025 --> 01:00:09,219
Anything you want,

872
01:00:10,112 --> 01:00:11,112
I'll get it for you.

873
01:00:11,770 --> 01:00:13,386
If you want to make music,

874
01:00:13,487 --> 01:00:15,096
I'll build you a studio.

875
01:00:15,847 --> 01:00:17,678
If you want to be a singer,

876
01:00:18,117 --> 01:00:19,826
I'll set up a label for you.

877
01:00:20,315 --> 01:00:21,352
I'm telling you

878
01:00:22,085 --> 01:00:24,528
there's nothing in this
world I wouldn't give you.

879
01:00:28,191 --> 01:00:29,191
So this is…

880
01:00:30,075 --> 01:00:31,675
A father's love.

881
01:00:43,493 --> 01:00:45,044
Hey! My shirt!

882
01:00:45,164 --> 01:00:47,868
What the hell, Direk?
You said you'd give me anything.

883
01:00:48,072 --> 01:00:49,522
And you're stingy over one shirt?

884
01:00:52,515 --> 01:00:54,130
Have I ever told you I love you?

885
01:00:56,223 --> 01:00:57,385
Don't know.

886
01:00:58,065 --> 01:01:01,114
But hey, you don't have to...

887
01:01:01,462 --> 01:01:03,278
Direk, I love you.

888
01:01:03,549 --> 01:01:06,922
- I said you don't have to—
- Dad, I love you.

889
01:01:07,010 --> 01:01:09,125
- You idiot.
- Dad.

890
01:01:21,816 --> 01:01:23,630
Did you tease Direk or something?

891
01:01:24,680 --> 01:01:26,392
He walked off muttering to himself.

892
01:01:27,226 --> 01:01:28,660
Nope.

893
01:01:36,924 --> 01:01:38,322
What are you thinking about?

894
01:01:41,491 --> 01:01:42,842
Just thinking.

895
01:01:43,937 --> 01:01:45,475
I'm lucky I met you.

896
01:01:47,376 --> 01:01:49,958
Arthit's lucky to have
met so many good people.

897
01:01:53,721 --> 01:01:54,721
Yeah.

898
01:01:55,447 --> 01:01:57,617
Especially Direk, who
raised me all these years.

899
01:01:58,742 --> 01:01:59,832
He's been my father,

900
01:02:00,032 --> 01:02:01,108
and my friend.

901
01:02:01,995 --> 01:02:03,592
No matter what I am,

902
01:02:04,177 --> 01:02:05,374
he's always loved me.

903
01:02:06,968 --> 01:02:07,968
And those guys too.

904
01:02:09,856 --> 01:02:11,684
Fah, Hill, Jo.

905
01:02:13,568 --> 01:02:15,025
They may fight like that,

906
01:02:17,693 --> 01:02:18,991
but they've never left my side.

907
01:02:20,875 --> 01:02:22,164
They're always there to help me,

908
01:02:24,017 --> 01:02:25,862
always supporting me.

909
01:02:26,998 --> 01:02:28,616
Including the day I met you.

910
01:02:30,317 --> 01:02:32,394
That was the luckiest thing in my life.

911
01:02:36,257 --> 01:02:38,460
You fit me perfectly in every way.

912
01:02:40,328 --> 01:02:42,158
As long as you're by my side,

913
01:02:44,411 --> 01:02:46,751
I can do anything in this world,

914
01:02:48,281 --> 01:02:50,063
no matter how hard it is.

915
01:02:51,933 --> 01:02:53,688
Just hold your hand,

916
01:02:55,617 --> 01:02:56,882
and I'll get through it.

917
01:02:59,362 --> 01:03:00,832
I feel the same.

918
01:03:02,134 --> 01:03:04,568
I feel like I can do anything,

919
01:03:05,414 --> 01:03:07,216
and do it well.

920
01:03:08,365 --> 01:03:09,908
I can go anywhere,

921
01:03:11,082 --> 01:03:13,029
as long as you're with me.

922
01:03:15,300 --> 01:03:16,300
No, it's me

923
01:03:17,771 --> 01:03:18,807
who's lucky.

924
01:03:20,453 --> 01:03:21,453
No, I am.

925
01:03:23,475 --> 01:03:25,481
Then we're both lucky.

926
01:03:27,281 --> 01:03:29,429
I'm lucky to have you.

927
01:03:31,115 --> 01:03:32,115
You

928
01:03:32,321 --> 01:03:33,688
are lucky to have me.

929
01:03:35,681 --> 01:03:37,408
We're both lucky.

930
01:03:40,974 --> 01:03:41,974
I love you.

931
01:03:44,710 --> 01:03:46,121
More than anything in the world.

932
01:03:49,965 --> 01:03:51,189
I love you too.
